grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 [&amp;_&gt;_*:last-child]:mb-0 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">This looks genuinely good — real progress. Solid layout, consistent color coding across all charts, visible borders, clean title, and you added the donut chart upgrade (Contract distribution) on top of the original four. This works well as your README preview image.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>A few things worth tightening before you save it as final:</strong></p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>The Card (26.54%) still has a lot of empty space</strong> at the bottom relative to the other tiles — it's better than before, but still noticeably taller than it needs to be. Quick fix: click it, drag the bottom edge up so it's closer to a square that matches the visual weight of the donut/bar charts next to it.</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>No insight callouts yet.</strong> We talked earlier about adding short 1-2 sentence text boxes near each chart (e.g., "42.71% churn for month-to-month vs. 2.83% for two-year contracts" near the donut). Right now the dashboard shows data but doesn't say anything — a viewer has to do the interpretation themselves. This is optional but would meaningfully strengthen it.</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Missing your MonthlyCharges finding's numbers on the chart itself</strong> — the bar chart shows relative bar lengths but no visible values. Not essential, but data labels (right-click chart → Format → Data labels → On) would make it more scannable without needing to hover.</li>
</ol>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>If you want to ship it as-is:</strong> it's genuinely presentable right now — clean, correctly labeled, consistent, and answers all 4 of your sub-questions visually (churn rate, contract, tenure, tech support) plus pricing. Good enough to use.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>To finalize for the README:</strong></p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Save this exact image (right-click → Save image as, or it's already a screenshot you have) as <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">dashboard_overview.png</code>.</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Upload it to <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">dashboard/screenshots/</code> in your repo.</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">The README's <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">![Churn Dashboard](./dashboard/screenshots/dashboard_overview.png)</code> line will then render this image right at the top of your repo page.</li>
</ol>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Do you want to add the insight callouts and data labels first (10 more minutes of polish), or ship this version now and move on to finalizing the README?</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-message-action-bar="" class="flex justify-start ml-0.5"><div class="text-text-300"><div role="toolbar" aria-label="Message actions" class="text-text-300 flex select-none items-stretch justify-between"><button type="button" data-cds="Button" data-size="xs" class="cds-reset group/btn relative isolate inline-flex shrink-0 items-center justify-center gap-1.5 whitespace-nowrap select-none cursor-[var(--cds-cursor-interactive)] aria-disabled:cursor-default data-[disabled]:cursor-default border-0 outline-none rounded h-control font-sans text-body font-medium [&amp;:disabled:not([aria-busy])]:opacity-50 disabled:pointer-events-none transition-shadow duration-fast focus-visible:shadow-focus text-primary aria-pressed:text-accent aspect-square w-control px-0 !text-muted hover:!text-primary" aria-label="Copy" data-testid="action-bar-copy" id="_r_4cg_" tabindex="0"><span aria-hidden="true" class="absolute -z-[1] rounded-[inherit] transition-colors duration-fast group-focus-visible/btn:shadow-[inset_0_0_0_1px_var(--cds-page-bg)] bg-transparent group-hover/btn:bg-fill-ghost-hover group-aria-expanded/btn:bg-fill-ghost-hover inset-0 group-aria-pressed/btn:bg-accent group-hover/btn:group-aria-pressed/btn:bg-accent cds-btn-squish "></span><span class="inline-flex min-w-0 items-center gap-1 "><span class="relative"><span data-cds="Icon" class="transition-all opacity-100 scale-100" aria-hidden="true" style="font-family: var(--font-anthropicons, Anthropicons-Variable); font-feature-settings: &quot;liga&quot; 0; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-style: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; line-height: 1; width: 1em; height: 1em; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; flex-shri